body:
## Steps to Reproduce

1. Install a language pack (https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/13710-chinese-simplified-language-pack----) and enable it.
2. Install the Flutter plugin.
3. Run a Flutter app.

Result:
Unable to see the output in Flutter's run window.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6748077/100877713-2271c000-34e4-11eb-8ff7-db3d4f8b519d.png)

There is also a related issue reported in the IDEA's issue tracker: https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/IDEA-256495

## Version info

I can reproduce this issue in the IDEA 2020.3 (Flutter plugin version: 51.0.4, Chinese language pack plugin version: 203.500.

comment_data.body: I guess the language pack has been updated to solve this problem. I verified that all three language packs published by JetBrains (Chinese, Japanese, and Korean) work properly now.

> I also noticed that I could see output if I click the debug button, but I can't see the output if I click the run button.

Since I almost always use the debug button I'll take another look using the run button.
I can reproduce the problem using the Run button. Since the Debug button works as expected I'm lowering the priority.

A user [here](https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/IDEA-269187) told that deleting the translated `debugger.session.tab.console.content.name` property in `XDebuggerBundle.properties` in language pack plugin helps.
I haven't tried it. But the original value of the `debugger.session.tab.console.content.name` is `Console`. You may check if the related flutter code uses hardcoded value like below (not sure if it is root cause) https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/blob/f16fb41436ed8aa88e62a224fb84a511a5eca271/src/io/flutter/run/FlutterDebugProcess.java#L150
